header.gameNote: O'REILLY AUTO PARTS PUERTO RICO TIP-OFF

article.headline: Fairfield 61, Chattanooga 42
article.story: SAN JUAN, Puerto Rico -- Greg Nero scored 17 points to lead Fairfield to a 61-42 victory over Chattanooga on Sunday. In addition, Herbie Allen scored 9 points for Fairfield (2-3) and Jonathan Han added 8. Chattanooga, which extends its winless streak to five games, was led by Nicchaeus Doaks who scored 15 points. Khalil Hartwell scored another 11 points for Chattanooga. Fairfield was first on the scoreboard during the game with a 3-pointer by Han and the team stayed in the lead throughout. By the end of the first half, Fairfield had a 25-16 lead.
